00:57:54.920 --> 00:57:59.450
around this time, 1509 and
in the years just after that,

00:57:59.450 --> 00:58:06.000
representing Ferdinand in marble
in the capacity of being a defender

00:58:06.000 --> 00:58:07.730
of Christendom against the Turk.

00:58:07.730 --> 00:58:11.510 position:56%
And, you know, in Italy I think that
the discourse is really much more

00:58:11.510 --> 00:58:14.130
about the Turks because
they're closer to the Turks.

00:58:14.130 --> 00:58:17.680 position:56%
Whereas in Iberia proper, the
discourse is much more about Muslims

00:58:17.680 --> 00:58:20.540
in North Africa and
there's a distinction drawn

00:58:20.540 --> 00:58:23.510
between these different
types of Muslims.

00:58:23.510 --> 00:58:26.820
The Turks are recent
arrivals relatively speaking

00:58:26.820 --> 00:58:28.120
in Mediterranean.

00:58:28.120 --> 00:58:29.870
But at any rate, yeah, in Italy,

00:58:29.870 --> 00:58:32.530
the way that this is
represented visually is

00:58:32.530 --> 00:58:36.970
as Ferdinand protecting Italy
from the Turkish expansion.

00:58:36.970 --> 00:58:41.730
And in Iberia proper, again, there
is wonderful imagery of this.

00:58:41.730 --> 00:58:44.430
Ferdinand actually participates
in a number of triumphal entries

00:58:44.430 --> 00:58:48.490
into Iberian cities, into
Valladolid, into Seville,

00:58:48.490 --> 00:58:51.550
and there's been some really good
work done analyzing the kinds

00:58:51.550 --> 00:58:56.140 position:56%
